race.comment: AZTEC DANCER (9) turned in a fine effort to win at this track and distance last start in a much-improved run. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot repeat the dose. IN LOVE (2) gave a sight here last time, leading until claimed in the straight. Blinkers come off now and this does look easier. KALOSYNI (6) was well in the market first up from a spell last start over 1050m at Morphettville but was safely held. Gone back to the jumpouts and can improve sharply with that run out of the way. EFFUSIV (10) progressed nicely last time out to finish just a head from the winner at headquarters. Doesn't need to improve much to go one better. RICH LADY (11) has been freshened with 50 days, keeping the legs ticking over with a Strathalbyn trial win. Goes well here and is among the main chances.
